SpatiumDDI appliance state directory.

Files dropped here on first boot or by cloud-init user-data:

  .env             Generated by spatiumddi-firstboot on first power-on.
                   Holds POSTGRES_PASSWORD / SECRET_KEY /
                   CREDENTIAL_ENCRYPTION_KEY / DNS_AGENT_KEY /
                   DHCP_AGENT_KEY / SPATIUMDDI_VERSION /
                   COMPOSE_PROFILES. Edit + restart the stack to
                   apply changes.

  release          Optional. Set SPATIUMDDI_VERSION=<calver-tag> to pin
                   a specific release at first boot. cloud-init can
                   write this via:
                     write_files:
                       - path: /etc/spatiumddi/release
                         content: SPATIUMDDI_VERSION=2026.05.07-1

  agent.env        Optional. For distributed agent appliances (Phase 4
                   of the appliance roadmap, not Phase 1) — points a
                   DNS-only or DHCP-only appliance at an external
                   control plane.

The compose file lives at /usr/local/share/spatiumddi/docker-compose.yml
and resolves variables from this directory's .env (symlinked in by
spatiumddi-firstboot). The appliance ships Debian's `docker-compose`
(Python v1 binary, hyphenated syntax). To upgrade to upstream
Docker's `docker compose` plugin, see appliance/README.md.

Operator commands:
  spatiumddi-stack-status              docker compose ps + version pin + health
  systemctl status spatiumddi-firstboot
  systemctl restart spatiumddi-firstboot   # re-runs after editing .env
  journalctl -u spatiumddi-firstboot -f    # systemd transitions
  tail -f /var/log/spatiumddi/firstboot.log    # full orchestrator output
